cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper focuses on the analysis of the generalized mutual information (GMI) for the mixed-analog-to-digital converter (ADC) architecture in frequency-selective channels. 
2. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper deals with the design of a frequency-domain equalizer for mitigating inter-carrier interference in multi-carrier techniques, such as orthogonal frequency division multiplexing, and its application to multi-user scenarios. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a mixed-ADC architecture for massive multiple-input-multiple-output (MIMO) systems and analyzes its performance in static and time-varying single-input-multiple-output (SIMO) channels. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the use of multi-carrier techniques and frequency-domain equalization for handling inter-symbol interference in mixed-ADC massive MIMO uplink. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper proposes a novel mixed-ADC architecture for MIMO systems and evaluates its performance in frequency-selective channels.
